x=\frac{\pi}{2}
\sin\left(2 \times \frac{\pi}{2}\right)  =  \sin\left({\pi}\right) = 0
2 \times \sin\left(\frac{\pi}{2}\right)  =  2 \times \sin\left(\frac{\pi}{2}\right) = 2.
 \sin\left(2 x\right) = 2 \sin(x) \cos(x).
